SIMPLE: steadfast
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Steadfast
<hw>Stead"fast</hw> <pr>(-f⟦adot⟧st)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Stead</ets> + <ets>fast</ets>, that is, fast in place.]</ety>
<ety>[Written also <ets>stedfast</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Firmly
fixed or established; fast fixed; firm.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧This
<xex>steadfast</xex> globe of earth.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not fickle or wavering; constant; firm; resolute;
unswerving; steady.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Steadfast</xex> eye.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Abide <qex>steadfast</qex> unto him [thy neighbor] in the time of
his trouble.</q> <rj><qau>Ecclus. xxii. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whom resist <qex>steadfast</qex> in the faith.</q> <rj><qau>1 Pet.
v. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steadfastly</ent>⟦br⟧
